Negw.073

714695f-a.title: Manhattan: 86th Street (East) - York Avenue
714695f-a.text:
(1)
Dobbs Health Station and Ifant Clinic, 519 East 86th Street,
north side, east of York Avenue. The wing of this building is
a frame structure.
N7  NW0A 3951  August 2, 1927
P. L. Sperr
(2)
The same, showing the adjoining house, which is No. 517.
1932
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York
Negative No. 237
The New York Sun of December 22, 1938 reports the filing of
plans for a modern, 6 story apartment on the present site of
Nos. 517-21 E. 86th Street. This structure, at a cost of ~175,000
will rise to the west of Misercorde Hospital and stand where the
three buildings in the larger view are.
